			<title>Kickstarter: TA style RTS</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?74019-Kickstarter-TA-style-RTS&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Fri, 24 Aug 2012 18:28:36 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>Thought this might interest some of you. A small gaming studio wants to make a Total Annihilation styled RTS game. I will link the concept video below. The game is titled Planetary Annihilation, and the only other game the studio has made that I am aware of is Monday Night Combat, a fairly well...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Thought this might interest some of you. A small gaming studio wants to make a Total Annihilation styled RTS game. I will link the concept video below. The game is titled Planetary Annihilation, and the only other game the studio has made that I am aware of is Monday Night Combat, a fairly well received third person dota styled shooter.<br />
<br />
I think it looks pretty interesting, but there are a few problems.<br />
<br />
1) I think the concept they are promising is going to be harder/more expensive to pull off than they might expect. I get the feeling it will be simplified in the final product, which might make pc elitists angry.<br />
<br />
2) They are asking a lot for a Kickstarter. There have only been a few breakout successes using Kickstarter as a source of funding that I am aware of so far. That Shadowrun project I linked awhile back, for example, has been unable to achieve the requested funding, last I checked.<br />
<br />
Edit: I guess I'm just pessimistic, they already have 700k of the 900k they requested. <br />
<br />
For those that don't want to watch the video, here is a short summary of what you see in it:<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>summary</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
<br />
The graphic style presented is very simple and cartoony, they almost look like legos. I thought they were reasonable considering the budget, but some people will be put off.<br />
<br />
So the game starts off exactly how you would expect TA or SC to. A robot is called down, starts building a base, then robot armies start fighting each other. You notice in the process, however, that the battlefield map is spherical, like Spore.<br />
<br />
The action cuts back to the base, the player opens a GUI that lets them designate the nearby moon, and they launch a robot to build a base on it. The lunar base then sends new units to the battlefield on the planet with what looks like artillery.<br />
<br />
The robots on the moon base are then told to access the nearby asteroid belt. They build engines on an asteroid, and send it plummeting towards the enemy base. Defense missiles are fired, but the asteroid still wrecks most of the planet. Hence the game's name: Planetary Annihilation.<br />
 
</div>
</div>
</div><br />
<br />
So what do you guys think? Is this something that would excite you?<br />
<br />

<iframe class="restrain" title="YouTube video player" width="640" height="390" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/FhEYvOYceNs?wmode=opaque" frameborder="0"></iframe>
</div>

]]></content:encoded>
